Upon completion of this course, the learner will be able to:
• consider real-world problems and determine appropriate optimization models (linear or nonlinear, continuous, integer, or mixed-integer) to use;
• apply simplex methods to solve continuous linear optimization problems and interpret the solutions using duality theory;
• describe main ideas of behind integer and mixed-integer optimization solution methods, especially their connections to continuous linear optimization methods;
• recognize some basic nonlinear optimization methods and their potential limitations based on model characteristics (convex versus nonconvex) and solution goals (local versus global solutions).
